highly_rated_on_rotten_tomatoes.title: Highly Rated on Rotten Tomatoes
highly_rated_on_rotten_tomatoes.description: Movies that have gotten the seal of approval from viewers and critics on Rotten Tomatoes.

65291.title: XXY
65291.description: When an intersex teenager comes of age, she asks difficult questions about her gender identity and makes a decision that will impact her future.

255739.title: A Monster in Paris
255739.description: Experiments gone wrong and a chemical explosion results in a monster unleashed in Paris, but he might not be as dangerous as everyone thought.

257360.title: Sleepaway Camp
257360.description: Following the death of her family, Angela is sent to a camp for the summer. After her arrival, brutal accidents begin to kill the other campers.

289816.title: Ghost In The Shell
289816.description: See the groundbreaking original before the release of the live-action remake starring Scarlett Johansson! It is 2029 and a female cyborg hunts a hacker who robs humans of their memories.

299580.title: The Big Easy
299580.description: A new female district attorney is unhappy with the gangs and corruption in New Orleans and bonds with a detective in this sultry crime thriller.

300449.title: Eight Men Out
300449.description: A dramatization about the infamous 1919 "Black Sox Scandal," in which eight members of the Chicago White Sox conspired with gamblers to throw the World Series in return for cash.

300454.title: Moonstruck
300454.description: Loretta Castorini (Cher), a bookkeeper from Brooklyn, New York, finds herself in a difficult situation when she falls for the brother of the man she has agreed to marry.

303190.title: The Usual Suspects
303190.description: The lone survivor of a heist-gone-wrong tells the feds how it all went down as they search for the enigmatic crime lord behind the disaster.

304797.title: Benny & Joon
304797.description: A quirky, romantic drama about two misfits who come together as a result of an unusual poker game.

306935.title: Lars and The Real Girl
306935.description: A delusional young man strikes up an unconventional relationship with a doll he finds on the Internet in this weird and warm comedy.

306938.title: Of Mice and Men
306938.description: In this adaptation of John Steinbeck's classic novel, a migrant worker looks after his dimwitted, gentle-giant friend during the Great Depression.

310136.title: Hotel Rwanda
310136.description: The true story of a brave hotel manager who risked his and his family’s lives to harbor over 1,000 refugees during the 1994 Rwandan genocide.

310149.title: The Secret of NIMH
310149.description: In this animated adventure, a timid mouse seeks help from a colony of intelligent rats to save her family, but the rats have their own problems.

310154.title: 12 Angry Men
310154.description: A twelve-person jury becomes increasingly tense with arguments continuing into the night as one juror must convince the other eleven he is right.

312175.title: Dirty Rotten Scoundrels
312175.description: Who will emerge as the ultimate hustler when a sophisticated con man and a free-wheeling huckster compete to scam an heiress out of $50,000?

312184.title: The Last Waltz
312184.description: This classic concert documentary focuses on The Band’s farewell concert in San Francisco, where they are joined by a number of special musical guests.

312417.title: Hoosiers
312417.description: A man gets a last chance at redemption by coaching a small-town Indiana high-school basketball team and bring his team to the 1951 state championship.

316454.title: Secretary
316454.description: Hoping to recover from her troubled past, a socially awkward woman becomes a secretary for an eccentric lawyer who is aroused by her obedience.

326245.title: Dial M For Murder
326245.description: When an ex-tennis pro’s plan to murder his cheating wife and steal her inheritance goes awry, he must find a way to evade the law.

326260.title: Suspiria
326260.description: A series of gruesome murders and inexplicable events lead a new student to suspect something evil is at play at a prestigious ballet academy.

334159.title: The Return of the Living Dead
334159.description: While working at a medical supply company, two employees release a gas that raises the dead, causing the town to be overrun with flesh-eating zombies.

356528.title: Bowling for Columbine
356528.description: This documentary examines gun violence in the U.S. in relation to other countries, including the specific events that led to the Columbine massacre.

356529.title: A Fish Called Wanda
356529.description: After pulling off a diamond heist, the motley crew of culprits dupe one another repeatedly in hopes of pocketing the loot, in this black comedy.

358570.title: Bubba Ho-Tep
358570.description: An aging Elvis joins forces with a fellow nursing home resident who believes he's JFK to fight a mummy who wants to steal the souls of the elderly.

371078.title: A Most Wanted Man
371078.description: When a mysterious immigrant arrives in Hamburg, he attracts the attention of U.S. and German intelligence, kicking off a race to uncover the truth.

376133.title: Teeth
376133.description: During a traumatic assault, a repressed teen finds out her vagina has protective teeth and uses this discovery as a source of empowerment and revenge.

385498.title: Arbitrage
385498.description: In this electrifying thriller, a hedge-fund magnate's fortunes turn when a deadly error threatens to destroy both his financial empire and his family.

389503.title: Robocop
389503.description: A cop who died in the line of duty is transformed into a chrome-plated cyborg policeman with an indestructible new body and a thirst for revenge.

400850.title: Meatballs
400850.description: In this classic comedy, camp counselor Tripper guides a collection of lovable campers and libidinous staff through the pleasures of a coed summer,

404623.title: Battle Royale
404623.description: A group of students from a Japanese high school are forced to compete in a battle, killing one another until only one is left standing.

405451.title: Rescue Dawn
405451.description: Based on the true story of a captured German-American fighter pilot in the Vietnam War who plans a daring escape after suffering abuse by his captors.

417716.title: Buffalo 66
417716.description: Billy Brown just got out of jail. Now he’s going to serve some real time. He’s going home.

438040.title: The World's Fastest Indian
438040.description: An eccentric racer takes his custom-built motorcycle to America with hopes of setting the world land-speed record in this inspiring true story.

438042.title: Goon
438042.description: A bouncer looking for purpose takes his fighting skills to the hockey rink where his epic brawls could make him a star—if he can learn how to skate.

441470.title: Super Size Me

441476.title: A Brilliant Young Mind
441476.description: A socially awkward teenage math prodigy finds new confidence and new friendships when he lands a spot on the British squad at the International Mathematics Olympiad.

448257.title: Amores Perros
448257.description: A horrific car accident connects the lives of three strangers: a lovesick dog fighter, an injured supermodel and a hitman running from his past.

448663.title: Leaving Las Vegas

456876.title: Bad Lieutenant: Port of Call New Orleans

456902.title: Trust

460204.title: King of New York

465170.title: Goodnight Mommy

474070.title: We Are What We Are

475822.description: Foreign Language Oscar-winner about a recently unemployed cellist musician who ends up taking a job preparing the dead for their funerals.

475898.title: Heathers
475898.description: When a snobbish high school clique threatens to ruin her reputation, a teenage girl teams up with a sociopath and plots to kill the cool kids.

480284.title: Bernie

480291.title: Triangle

487757.description: This true story of a woman with a tortured past traces her path from prostitution, to hopeful love, to vengeful murder, to becoming a serial killer.

487965.title: James White
487965.description: With a sick mother who needs his care, a young man tries to put his reckless lifestyle behind him and avoid temptation in New York City.

491807.title: Ginger Snaps
491807.description: Although they’re obsessed with death, two sisters are not prepared to handle when one of them is bitten by a werewolf, in this coming-of-age drama.

499404.title: The Texas Chain Saw Massacre
499404.description: After a run-in with a group of cannibals, a young woman and her friends are terrorized by Leatherface and his chainsaw  in this classic slasher.

520213.title: Train to Busan (Dubbed)

524652.title: Coherence
524652.description: When eight friends gather for a dinner party on the night of an astronomical event, a series of unusual circumstances tests their relationships.

526368.title: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo
526368.description: In this adaptation of Stieg Larsson's novel, hacker Lisbeth Salander teams up with a journalist to investigate a murder connected to a rich family.

526990.title: Re-Animator
526990.description: Cult horror-shocker about a medical student and his girlfriend who conduct outrageous experiments with dead tissue after a new student arrives.

534021.title: Stronger
534021.description: A man who was maimed by the Boston Marathon bombing, becoming a double amputee, helps police find the terrorists while trying to heal from trauma.

539677.title: Lion
539677.description: A young man makes an emotional journey to reconnect with his birth family in India after being tragically separated from them years earlier.

549640.title: Cartel Land
549640.description: A stark look at two Mexican drug cartel hot-spots and the two separate vigilante groups who've taken justice to eradicate crime into their own hands.

550636.title: The Void
550636.description: After Sheriff Deputy Carter finds an injured man on the side of the road, he takes him to a hospital where chaos and insanity break out.

550824.title: The Hunger Games
550824.description: In a dystopian future, 16-year-old Katniss volunteers to take her younger sister’s place in a battle where children must fight to stay alive.

550826.title: The Hunger Games: Catching Fire
550826.description: As Katniss and Peeta embark on their victory tour, President Snow plans an even deadlier new Hunger Games, which threatens the future of Panem.

551307.title: Audition
551307.description: In his search for a new wife, a widowed TV producer stages a dating service to screen women and finds one who isn't quite as perfect as her audition.

551323.title: I Am Not a Witch
551323.description: Critically acclaimed satire about villagers in Zambia who charge an 8-year-old, who shows up with no parents, as a witch to be sentenced to exile.

556638.title: The Green Prince
556638.description: After retiring to the U.S., the Palestinian son of a founding leader of Hamas, voluntarily outs himself as a mole for the Israeli secret service.

559330.title: Attack the Block
559330.description: A teen gang must defend their neighborhood from savage aliens who turn their apartment complex into an intergalactic warzone.

566803.title: A Man Called Ove
566803.description: When a boisterous Persian family, including a pregnant woman, moves next door to the neighborhood’s grumpy old man, unexpected love and kinship bloom.

568448.title: The Night Eats the World
568448.description: What seems like a nightmare is a horrifying reality for a man who wakes up in Paris as apparently the only survivor of a swarm of killer zombies.

579379.title: Super Dark Times
579379.description: Two teen boys and best friends see their calm suburban world implode after the accidental death of a classmate leads to another death they can’t hide.

579647.title: Fahrenheit 9/11
579647.description: The definitive exposé revealing how and why the Bush Administration manufactured evidence to invade war in Iraq following the 2001 terrorist attacks.

580530.title: Detroit
580530.description: This relevant, fact-based story, set in 1967’s Detroit riots, tracks a group of rogue cops, who respond to a call with vengeance instead of justice.

582081.title: Vicky Cristina Barcelona
582081.description: Two American women are taken in by the splendor of Spain, but not as much as they are drawn to a rugged painter and his sultry former lover.

582789.title: Breath
582789.description: Two friends enjoy surfing while living their teenage years in 1970s Australia, but an encounter with an elder surfer changes the course of their lives.

585776.title: Burning
585776.description: A man agrees to watch an ex-neighbor’s cat while she goes on a trip and becomes suspicious of the man she brings back just before her disappearance.

588324.title: Professor Marston and the Wonder Women (En)
588324.description: Here’s the true origins story of a modern-day feminist superhero – Wonder Woman – and the psychologist-inventor who created the powerful character.

589091.title: American Animals
589091.description: The true story of four young men who feel their lives are like a movie and attempt to steal a rare and valuable book from a Kentucky University.

589490.title: Starfish
589490.description: Cassette tapes left behind by her dead BFF helps Aubrey navigate the apocalypse that arrived the day of the funeral when alien beasts attacked Earth.

595588.title: In the Fade (Dubbed)
595588.description: After a woman’s family is killed in a terrorist attack, she will stop at nothing to make sure the murderers get their fair share of justice.

599075.title: Styx
599075.description: ER doctor Rike embarks on a solitary quest in the open ocean to preserve herself and the lives of the refugees she encounters.

599086.title: The Third Wife
599086.description: After becoming the third wife to a wealthy landowner in 19th century Vietnam, May struggles with family and the prospects of motherhood.

599603.title: Contagion
599603.description: Oscar®-winning filmmaker Steven Soderbergh (Ocean's Eleven films, Traffic) returns to large-scale cinema with this global action thriller that revolves around the threat of a deadly outbreak of a fatal disease and the people determined to keep it at bay. As the fast-moving epidemic grows, the worldwide medical community races to find a cure and control the panic that spreads faster than the virus itself. At the same time, ordinary people struggle to survive in a society coming apart. A stellar international ensemble cast including Academy Award® winners Matt Damon, Gwyneth Paltrow, Kate Winslet, Marion Cotillard and nominees Jude Law and Laurence Fishburne portray the dedicated doctors at the CDC and World Health Organization who rush to contain the outbreak of a new virus. Tracking its source to Hong Kong and searching for a cure, these determined Samaritans do their utmost to limit deaths, civil unrest and the false rumors surrounding the disease in this viral outbreak drama with multiple plot lines in the style of Soderbergh's Oscar®-winning narcotics drama Traffic.

599629.title: Eyes Wide Shut
599629.description: Tom Cruise and Nicole Kidman star as a married couple entangled in an intricate web of jealousy and sexual obsession in Stanley Kubrick's final cinematic offering.  At a Christmas party hosted by wealthy, unconventional Victor Ziegler (Sydney Pollack), provocative advances and innocent flirtations arouse suspicion as high-society physician Dr. William Harford (Cruise) and his sexy wife, Alice (Kidman) watch each other from a distance. Alone later, this seemingly perfect couple confront their intimate sexual fantasies--which don't include each other.  Caught between reality and illusion, jealousy and obsession, William struggles with his inner urges. Will he act on his erotic fantasies or keep them hidden deep inside? Sometimes a man can see more clearly with his Eyes Wide Shut.

599997.title: Wedding Crashers
599997.description: Owen Wilson (Starsky & Hutch) and Vince Vaughn (Old School) star as John Beckwith and Jeremy Klein, two partying divorce attorneys--and committed womanizers--who have figured out a surefire way to meet women: they crash weddings. But the guys' happy-go-lucky lives change abruptly when John unexpectedly falls in love with a bridesmaid (Rachel McAdams - The Notebook). Things become even more complicated when the men discover that the object of John's affection is the daughter of the United States Secretary of the Treasury (Christopher Walken - Catch Me If You Can) in the engaging romantic comedy Wedding Crashers.

602287.title: Princess Cyd
602287.description: A 16-year-old leaves her depressed father to visit her novelist aunt in Chicago over the summer, where she falls for a neighbor girl.

607451.title: E.T. The Extra-Terrestrial
607451.description: A boy forms a special bond with a sweet and gifted alien from another planet. He tries to keep it a secret, but he needs help to keep the visitor safe.

610572.title: Goodfellas
610572.description: Based on a true story, a young man rises up the ranks of a mob family over several years, dabbling in drugs, heists and murders along the way.

614727.title: The Miseducation of Cameron Post

617447.title: Pretty Woman
617447.description: Julia Roberts stars as a witty prostitute who charms a serious businessman, as the two unlikely lovers fall for each other over the course of a week.

628970.title: Hellboy II: The Golden Army
628970.description: Hellboy and his crew of paranormal outcasts face off with forces of darkness in this imaginative adventure from visionary director Guillermo del Toro.

637827.title: Don Jon
637827.description: A Jersey guy addicted to porn meets a charming and beautiful woman whom he hopes to pursue a real relationship with, but his habits get in the way.

637929.title: Carlito's Way

640031.title: Blackfish

640302.title: Giant Little Ones

641484.title: Brown Sugar

642254.title: The Girl with All the Gifts

643081.title: West Side Story
643081.description: This electrifying musical, winner of ten Academy Awards, including Best Picture, reimagines “Romeo and Juliet,” set during gang warfare in 1950s NYC.

644877.title: Rio Lobo

646730.title: Fists of Fury

647690.title: What About Bob?

649963.title: Freaks
649963.description: A little girl who has been shut away from the outside world by her father soon discovers a dangerous universe awaiting beyond her front door.

652270.title: The Goonies

655009.title: Role Models

667137.title: 12 Angry Men

672301.title: The 40-Year-Old Virgin

676665.title: The Death of Stalin
676665.description: Follows the wild scramble for power inside the Council of Ministers upon the sudden illness and death of Soviet dictator Joseph Stalin in 1953.

676725.title: Boyhood
676725.description: Richard Linklater's acclaimed hit, filmed over twelve years with the same cast, is a groundbreaking celebration of life, growing up, and parenting.

676860.title: Bone Tomahawk

712866.title: Dog Soldiers

724713.title: Blue Is the Warmest Color
